    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VdjZR-h_YnH9"
      },
      "source": [
        "3. Handle missing values  \n",
        "- The first option to delete or ignore the data points with missing values is not recommended because this dataset has thousands of missing values per column. This strategy only works if a few rows contain missing data. If the rows with missing values were removed, most of the dataset would be lost.  \n",
        "- The second option to replace the missing values with the median of the corresponding attribute works well for APS datasets.\n",
        "- The third option to remove the entire attribute from the dataset only works when a feature is mostly missing.  \n",
        "\n",
        "For this project, the best option combines 2 and 3.  \n",
        "\n",
        "Step 1 - Remove extremely sparse features. Drop features with >80% missing values.  \n",
        "Step 2 - Impute remaining missing values. Use median replacement.  \n",
        "\n",
        "Pipeline:  \n",
        "\n",
        "Replace \"na\" -> NaN  \n",
        "       ↓  \n",
        "Remove features with >80% missing values  \n",
        "       ↓  \n",
        "Fill remaining missing values with median."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "t--DD8fdYoq0"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Identify features with excessive missing values\n",
        "# Compute the percentage of missing values for each feature\n",
        "missing_percent = x_train.isnull().mean()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Select features where fore than 80% values are missing\n",
        "columns = missing_percent[missing_percent > 0.8].index\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop feature with high percentages of missing values form both\n",
        "# the training and test sets\n",
        "x_train = x_train.drop(columns = columns)\n",
        "\n",
        "x_test = x_test.drop(columns = columns)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XjfrmkKOblaF"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Fill in the missing values with the median\n",
        "df_training = df_training.fillna(df_training.median(numeric_only=True))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lb3MiBzMvXOE"
      },
      "source": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "cY7WzljbbyEF",
        "outputId": "965a76b4-5957-41cb-99c7-058e69af4d31"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "np.int64(0)"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 34
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Verify that no missing values remain\n",
        "df_training.isnull().sum().sum()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jsPvHc_BiV3w"
      },
      "source": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JI7-JoTtiYXv"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Apply median imputation for feature matrices\n",
        "imputer = SimpleImputer(strategy=\"median\")\n",
        "\n",
        "x_train = imputer.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "x_test = imputer.transform(x_test)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T1apVXA5kQWD"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Logarithmix tranformation to reduce skewness\n",
        "x_train = np.log1p(x_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "x_test = np.log1p(x_test)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3f71ZChvkaI-"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Standardize the features\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "\n",
        "x_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
        "x_test_scaled = scaler.transform(x_test)"
      ]
    },
